-- Hidroconstructia Wins Water-Upgrade Contract in Romanian Town
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2013-02-06T11:02:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-06/hidroconstructia-wins-water-upgrade-contract-in-romanian-town.html
Hidroconstructia SA,  a Romanian
construction company, was awarded a 26.6 million lei ($8
million) contract to upgrade the water and sewage system in the
western town of Pecica.  Apa Arad SA, the Romanian utility that awarded the
contract, will use funds from the European Union to help finance
the improvements, according to a European Union  procurement
notice  published today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  